formalText: Struggling with finding a structure that works for them.
He found it very frustrating about how they need Tanya and her story.
Their view of things is not ideal and therefore bad it's naive then the converse is also naive nothing's perfect.
They feel since they are nit perfect so they might as well just not try to do anything at all.
They think they can't process what happened to them since they had some much happen at once.
He has been processing through his feelings a lot.

A couple weeks ago they talked about his wife's about anger and the sense in which one of them not the only but one of the causes of herself injury and suicidal suicide is her utter inability to deal with the anger from anyone else or herself.
